.mso an.tmac
.TH "DUNE-TRACE" 1 "" "Dune 3.23.0" "Dune Manual"
.\" Disable hyphenation and ragged-right
.nh
.ad l
.SH NAME
.P
dune\N'45'trace \N'45' Commands to view dune\N'39's event trace
.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
\fBdune trace\fR \fICOMMAND\fR …
.SH COMMANDS
.TP 4
\fBcat\fR [\fIOPTION\fR]…

.TP 4
\fBcommands\fR [\fB\N'45'\N'45'trace\N'45'file\fR=\fIFILE\fR] [\fIOPTION\fR]…
Display executed processes in shell format
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP 4
\fB\N'45'\N'45'help\fR[=\fIFMT\fR] (default=\fBauto\fR)
Show this help in format \fIFMT\fR\N'46' The value \fIFMT\fR must be one of \fBauto\fR, \fBpager\fR, \fBgroff\fR or \fBplain\fR\N'46' With \fBauto\fR, the format is \fBpager\fR or \fBplain\fR whenever the \fBTERM\fR env var is \fBdumb\fR or undefined\N'46'
.TP 4
\fB\N'45'\N'45'version\fR
Show version information\N'46'
.SH EXIT STATUS
.P
\fBdune trace\fR exits with:
.TP 4
0
on success\N'46'
.TP 4
1
if an error happened\N'46'
.TP 4
130
if it was interrupted by a signal\N'46'
.SH SEE ALSO
.P
dune(1)